# Integrate AI for Weather & Shipping Recommendation

We will replace the hardcoded Python heuristic logic for the "AI-powered shipping recommendation" with an actual AI model to provide a natural language summary of the weather alongside dynamic shipping advice. 

## Proposed Changes

### Backend (Python)
#### [MODIFY] app.py
- Install and configure `google-generativeai` (Google Gemini API). If you prefer OpenAI, we can substitute it easily.
- Update `/api/weather/<city>` and `/api/weather/coordinates` to call the AI with the OpenWeather JSON data.
- The prompt will ask the AI to "Provide a brief 1-2 sentence summary of the current weather and a clear shipping recommendation (Proceed, Caution, Delay, or Cancel) based on the conditions."
- We will return the natural language AI response to the frontend rather than the static [get_shipping_recommendation(data)](file:///c:/Personal/import-export/app.py#452-546) output.
- (Optional) We can replace or heavily modify the [get_shipping_recommendation](file:///c:/Personal/import-export/app.py#452-546) function to act as a fallback if the API fails or entirely remove it and let the LLM handle all the reasoning.

### Frontend (HTML/JS)
#### [MODIFY] templates/weather.html
- Update the `<div id="shippingContent">` to cleanly display the AI-generated text.
- Modify the display logic [displayShipping(s)](file:///c:/Personal/import-export/templates/weather.html#250-263) to render the custom AI summaries and recommendations instead of the static blocks.

## User Review Required

